6b7068983&oe=5F7E219F";}i:21;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:22;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:3102689406;}i:23;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:24;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:25;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:26;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2391077677329992453";}i:27;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEu0HqjnssF";}i:28;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599258692;}i:29;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:2226:"“𝑇ℎ𝑒 𝑙𝑖𝑔ℎ𝑡 𝑏𝑢𝑟𝑛𝑒𝑑 𝑠𝑜 𝑏𝑟𝑖𝑔ℎ𝑡𝑙𝑦 𝑖𝑛 𝑝𝑒𝑜𝑝𝑙𝑒’𝑠 ℎ𝑒𝑎𝑟𝑡𝑠, 𝑜𝑓 𝑡ℎ𝑜𝑠𝑒 𝑤ℎ𝑜 ℎ𝑎𝑑 𝑠𝑢𝑓𝑓𝑒𝑟𝑒𝑑 𝑠𝑜 𝑚𝑢𝑐ℎ, 𝑏𝑒𝑐𝑎𝑢𝑠𝑒 𝑡ℎ𝑒𝑦 𝑘𝑛𝑒𝑤 𝑙𝑖𝑓𝑒 𝑤𝑎𝑠 𝑎 𝑏𝑒𝑎𝑢𝑡𝑖𝑓𝑢𝑙 𝑡ℎ𝑖𝑛𝑔, 𝒂𝒏𝒅 𝒕𝒉𝒆𝒊𝒓 𝒔𝒖𝒇𝒇𝒆𝒓𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝒉𝒂𝒅 𝒎𝒂𝒅𝒆 𝒕𝒉𝒆𝒎 𝒂𝒘𝒂𝒓𝒆 𝒐𝒇 𝒍𝒊𝒇𝒆𝒔 𝒃𝒆𝒂𝒖𝒕𝒚“ 

That last part is so profound. 

Life 𝒊𝒔 a beautiful thing. 

We all unfortunately suffer at some point in our life. 

I believe we can see it like a true awakening. 

For me it was like I had been asleep for the first half of my life. 

Through the losses I have experienced, what I gained out of it was that life has its light side and it’s dark side. 

That we have the embrace both sides, acknowledge the light and the dark.

And when we do, life has a deeper meaning and we have a higher purpose.

✨ I can guide and support you to work through the light and the dark. 

✨ Help you embrace your loss.

✨ Support you in finding the meaning within your loss. 

✨ To see the beauty again. 

It’s a horrible experience, I know. 
But it doesn’t have to be all consuming. 

There is beauty in your life, let me support you to find that again. 

PM me, let me know your story, and how you want to return to love and find the beauty again. 

Lots of love sweet one. 
Sharna xx

