⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Last week (or maybe the week before - lockdown got my sense of time all messed) she cut FOUR new teeth up the top. She didn’t fuss at ALL and I probably wouldn’t have even noticed if she didn’t giggle when she was lying down, giving me a good view of her new pearly whites peeking through the gums. And now this week, she’s cutting two new bottom teeth! She’s a wee bit clingier this time around but still not fussy or grumpy. She’s a champ.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’m so proud of her for taking it all in her stride, and pretty chuffed that I can see myself in her personality. She might look like her da, but she soldiers on like her māmā.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Now to make sure she understands that she doesn’t always have to soldier on and she’s allowed to lean on other people when she’s going through tough stuff - something I’m still working on myself 
